#Delimiters are symbols used to structure Python code.
#They define boundaries of statements, blocks, collections, strings, and expressions.
#delimiters are symbols or characters that separate, enclose, or structure parts of the code.
# They are not operators.
"""| **Delimiter**  | **Name**             | **Function / Use in Python**                                                       |
| -------------- | -------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `' '` or `" "` | Quotes               | Used to **define string literals**.                                                |
| `()`           | Parentheses          | Used for **function calls**, **grouping expressions**, **tuples**, **parameters**. |
| `[]`           | Square brackets      | Used for **lists**, **indexing**, **slicing**.                                     |
| `{}`           | Curly braces         | Used for **dictionaries** and **sets**.                                            |
| `:`            | Colon                | Starts a **new indented block** (if, for, while, def, class).                      |
| `,`            | Comma                | Separates **items/arguments** in lists, tuples, function calls.                    |
| `.`            | Dot                  | Used for **member access** (object.attribute).                                     |
| `#`            | Hash / Pound         | Used for **comments**.                                                             |
| `\`            | Backslash            | Used as **escape character** in strings or **line continuation**.                  |
| `_`            | Underscore           | Used in identifiers, special names (`__init__`).                                   |
| `@`            | At symbol            | Used for **decorators**.                                                           |
| `;`            | Semicolon            | Allows **multiple statements in one line** (not recommended).                      |
| `=`            | Assignment delimiter | Assigns value to variable (also counted under operators).                          |
| `<>`           | Angle brackets       | Used internally in `<class>`, not used as operator.                                |
| `->`           | Arrow                | Used in **function annotations** (type hints).                                     |
| `...`          | Ellipsis             | Used in slicing and as placeholder (`pass` alternative).

                        |
"""